			<div id = "comment-20916" class = "comment">
				<p>The author is correct if you restrict your state to be a real vector, but this is not always the case. For example when analyzing the time-varying behavior of circuits with inductors and capacitors, we typically use the Laplace transform which let us use linear circuits analysis using complex vectors. For physical systems with springs and masses, you would also do the same. In this case a "stationary point" means that you find a solution which is constant in the _Laplace_ domain. In the _time_ domain, this is a periodic waveform which does not decay, which may not be a constant function.</p>
